#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:9
msgid "Canned Responses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:11
msgid ""
"This settings section lets you manage your personal boilerplates (aka "
"\"canned responses\") which are handy when replying to messages with "
":ref:`prepared responses<mail-compose-responses>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:16
msgid "Edit Reponses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:18
msgid ""
"The middle pane displays a list of saved responses. Select one to see its "
"name and text in the form on the right. You can right away edit both and "
"save the changes by clicking the *Save* button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:22
msgid ""
"If the fields are not editable and there's no *Save* button below, this is a"
" global response defined by the system administrator which cannot be edited."
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:28
msgid "Create a New Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:30
msgid ""
"Click the + icon in the responses list footer to create a new response. Give"
" it a name and enter the response text and finish with clicking the *Save* "
"button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:36
msgid "Delete a Reponse"
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:38
msgid ""
"The *Delete* button also located in the responses list footer will delete "
"the currently selected item after displaying a confirmation dialog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../en_US/settings/responses.rst:41
msgid ""
"The button may be grayed out for global responses managed by the system "
"administrator."
msgstr ""
